<note xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><term xml:lang="ta">paital</term> is not without problems semantically; it should be a kind of nominal derivation of pai <q>become green/pale</q> (though not the verbal noun of the 11th class = <term xml:lang="ta">paittal</term>). The TL gives, among others, the meanings "affliction" and "cold". The former might be derived from the second connotation of "become green", i.e. not the fresh sprouting of plants, but bodily decline. The latter, seemingly the only one to make sense here, is harder to justify, though the DEDR includes it under the same lemma 3821.</note></entry>
